Example

When running the script, enter the following values when prompted:

Enter a transition metal (e.g., W, Mo): Mo
Enter a chalcogen (e.g., Se, S, Te): Se
Enter supercell size along x (e.g., 1, 2): 2
Enter supercell size along y (e.g., 1, 2): 2
Enter supercell size along z (e.g., 1, 2): 1
Enter output filename prefix (e.g., TMD_structure): MoSe2_2x2x1

This example will create a 2x2x1 supercell of MoSe2 and save it in a file named MoSe2_2x2x1.cif. The structure will also be displayed using ASE's visualization tool.
Script Details

The create_tmd_structure function in the script:

    Defines lattice parameters for a 1H TMD structure.
    Builds a structure with the specified metal and chalcogen atoms.
    Scales the structure to the desired supercell size.
    Saves the structure to a CIF file.
    Converts the structure to an ASE Atoms object and opens a visualization window.
